{% extends 'base.html.twig' %}

{% block title %}Customer index{% endblock %}

{% block body %}

    <section id="how-it-works">
        <h2>How It Works</h2>
        <p>This page provides a platform for sending messages through channels to customers.</p>
        <p>To use the page:</p>
        <ol>
            <li>Navigate to the <a href="/customer">Customers</a> section to add new customers. Upon creation, a welcome message will be sent to the customer.</li>
            <li>Move to the <a href="/channel">Channels</a> section to create new channels for sending messages.</li>
            <li>In the <a href="/message">Messages</a> section, you can use the command line to send messages to specific channels. The syntax for sending messages is provided.</li>
            <li>To check if messages were sent successfully, you can inspect the log file located in <code>/var/log/messages.log</code>.</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

    <section id="create-customers">
        <h2>Create Customers</h2>
        <p>When you create a new customer, it sends a welcome message.</p>
        <!-- Your customer creation form goes here -->
    </section>

    <section id="create-channels">
        <h2>Create Channels</h2>
        <p>Create channels here.</p>
        <!-- Your channel creation form goes here -->
    </section>

    <section id="send-messages">
        <h2>Send Messages</h2>
        <p>You can send messages using the command line.</p>
        <p>To send a message, use the following syntax:</p>
        <pre>php bin/console app:send-message &lt;channelID&gt; &lt;type&gt; &lt;title&gt; &lt;message&gt;</pre>
        <p>To check if messages were sent, you can check the file located in <code>/var/log/messages.log</code>.</p>
    </section>

    <footer>
        <p>Thank you for visiting!</p>
    </footer>
    <title>About Page - How It Works</title>
